Apply the same pattern to `StampNode` (around line 236).

**4b. Spring drop animation.** In the `moveItemFromDrag` callback (around line 1850), after setting the final position via `updateItemMutation.mutate`, use Konva's built-in `Tween` to animate the node. Add an import-free approach since Konva Tween is available on node objects:

In the `onDragEnd` handler for stickers/stamps/notes (the anonymous functions at lines 1945, 1960, 1975, and also the draft variants), add a spring effect:
```jsx
onDragEnd={(event) => {
    const node = event?.target;
    if (node) {
        // Spring bounce effect
        node.to({
            scaleX: 1.06,
            scaleY: 0.94,
            duration: 0.1,
            onFinish: () => {
                node.to({
                    scaleX: 1,
                    scaleY: 1,
                    duration: 0.15,
                    easing: Konva.Easings.EaseOut
                });
            }
        });
    }
    moveItemFromDrag(item, event);
}}
```

Note: `node.to()` is Konva's built-in tween method available on any Konva node. No import needed since the `Stage`, `Layer` etc. are already imported from `react-konva`. However, for the `Easings` reference, add this import at the top of the file:
```jsx
import Konva from "konva";
```
The project already has `konva` as a dependency (since `react-konva` depends on it).

**4c. Enhance PuffEffect** (lines 404-461). Add more particles and a slight ring burst:
